    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bodies of electrically non-conducting material used for keeping charged conductors from contact with each other or from grounding and often also for supporting them. Usually refers to objects of glass or porcelain that support telephone or power lines, but that do not carry current.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042061/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>不導電的材質，用以將導電體隔開，或防止其接觸地面，通常也具支撐作用。通常指用於電話線或電線，不帶有電流之玻璃或陶瓷材料物件。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Körper aus elektrisch nichtleitendem Material, der dazu verwendet wird, den Kontakt zwischen stromführenden Leitern oder deren Erdung zu verhindern und häufig auch als deren Träger dient. Bezieht sich in der Regel auf Gebilde aus Glas oder Porzellan als Führung für Telefon- oder Stromkabel, die aber selbst nicht unter Strom stehen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
